+----------------------------------------------------------------+
                          Introduction
+----------------------------------------------------------------+

I have a boardgame called Mastermind. It's a really nice game 
and I like playing it! The only problem is that it requires a 
buddy :( Wouldn't it be nice if you could play alone... I 
thought. So I converted the game on to my dear Amiga! It's 
certenly not the first Mastermind clone around , but i think 
it's one of the best. Features are nice graphics, 
highscoresave and great gameplay. I hope you enjoy it!

+----------------------------------------------------------------+
                          Requirements
+----------------------------------------------------------------+

Well, an Amiga I guess :) Harddrive recomended (not tested 
without...)


It has been tested and proven to work on these computers:

Amiga1200 68020/14MHz, 2+4MB Ram, 500MB HD   <- My computer
Amiga1200 68030/50MHz, 2+16MB Ram, 850MB HD
Amiga1200 68020/28MHz, 2+4MB Ram, 120MB HD
Amiga4000 68040/25MHz, 2+16MB Ram, Lotsa HD :)
Amiga2000 68000, NTSC <- Now works on NTSC too!

